 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
<p>This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module to define a hierarchical organization of drawings, drawing sheets,
and drawing views, together with the administrative information necessary to
manage drawings and drawing sheets.</p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
<li><p>the structures for representing individual drawing revisions;</p>
</li>
<li><p> the hierarchical structure of drawings, drawing sheets; the
administrative data used for the purpose of drawing management; and</p>
</li>
<li><p> the administrative data used for the purpose of drawing management.</p>
</li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
<li><p>the exchange of drawing history;</p>
<note>Drawing history refers to prior drawing revisions.</note>
</li>
<li><p>the exchange of printer or plotter data used exclusively for the
creation of paper or hard copy versions of the drawing;</p>
<example>Printer or plotter data can be pen designations, plot
scale, or plot color specifications.</example>
</li> </outscope>

